            <div class="col-md-12">
              <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">Academic Honesty has become a prominent issue in educational and academic environments in recent times and is no longer restricted to copying homework from a friend or cheating in an examination. Academic Institutions understand that students cannot come up with their original work and therefore, allow the inclusion of other people’s work with the exception that the original author is appropriately acknowledged. </p>
              <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">Academic Dishonesty is a misdemeanour that students commit knowingly or unknowingly and the Academic Honesty module guides us so that we will never commit any form of Academic Dishonesty in the IB Program or throughout our academic journey. 
              </p>
              <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">
                Here’s an interview with our Academic Honesty Teacher, Mrs Sreevidya Devanand answering some of the frequently asked questions about Academic Honesty.
                  </p>

