            <div class="col-md-8">
                <p class="sub-title pad-bt15"><strong>Q: How would you introduce Academic Honesty to someone who has no clue what it is?</strong></p>
                
                <p class="sub-title pad-bt15"> I would like to change the word Academic Honesty to Academic Integrity, which is one of the fundamentals of learning. Academic dishonesty begins in elementary school and peaks in high school in some form. So, I will introduce Academic Honesty with simple instances of cheating in classrooms.</p>

                <p class="sub-title pad-bt15"><strong>Q: Are academic dishonesty and plagiarism the same thing?</strong></p>
                
                <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">Plagiarism is one of the most common forms of Academic Dishonesty.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-12">
              <p class="sub-title pad-bt15"><strong>Q: What are some practices that are considered Academically Dishonest that a lot of people might not know?</strong></p>
                
              <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">Working in collaboration when individual work is expected, knowingly helping others cheat or plagiarize, using a source that is prohibited, using photographs without permission can all count as Academic Dishonesty.</p>
