                <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">Students who get away with academic dishonesty might feel guilty in the long run and this might affect their self-esteem. Academic dishonesty might result in failure of grades. Sometimes students will have to face legal consequences and may result in loss of opportunities in future.</p>

                <p class="sub-title pad-bt15"><strong>Q: What are the best ways to prevent yourself from being Academically Dishonest?</strong></p>
                <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">Take responsibility, learn to manage your time, meet deadlines, reach out to your instructor, and seek help if needed, develop personal ethics and integrity. By all means cheating is not an option.</p>                
